    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1914-01-20T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1914-01-20T00:00:00-05:00" n="70"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d70">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 493.11/471.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to Minister
                            <persName type="to">Reinsch</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1914-01-20">
                            <hi rend="italic">January 20, 1914</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>No reply received to our January 13, but Department this morning has memorandum
                    from Chinese Legation saying the Foreign Office has cabled instructions for the
                    Legation to receive the balance due in same manner as in August. Department
                    accordingly will remit check for balance to Chinese Legation tomorrow. Please
                    advise Foreign Office immediately.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Bryan</hi>
                    </signed>.</closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
